  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) mandates\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crime Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n- Department of Justice\n- Banking regulators\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Internal control systems\n\n6. Enforcement Approaches\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalties\n- Regulatory sanctions\n- International cooperation\n\n7. Emerging Areas\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction tracking\n- Enhanced technological monitoring\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
